22/06/2007
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The Interior Ministry announced on Thursday (June 21st) that the former head of the Public Enterprise for Maintenance of Sports Facilities, Halil Paloshi, has been arrested on charges of abuse of office and embezzlement. Paloshi is accused of having caused over 1m euros in losses to the state. He was dismissed from his post in the state-run company two years ago, for administrative irregularities. (A1 TV, Makfax - 21/06/07) 
